Unsourced material may be challenged and removed. *Find sources:* "Maritime Square" subzone – news **·** newspapers **·** books **·** scholar **·** JSTOR *(July 2018)* *(Learn how and when to remove this message)* *(Learn how and when to remove this message)*Subzone of Bukit Merah Planning Area in Central Region, Singapore **Maritime Square** ([Chinese](/wiki/Chinese_language): 海事广场) is a subzone within the planning area of [Bukit Merah](/wiki/Bukit_Merah), [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore), as defined by the [Urban Redevelopment Authority](/wiki/Urban_Redevelopment_Authority) (URA). Its boundary is made up of Henderson Road, Telok Blangah Way and Telok Blangah Rise in the north; Lower Delta Road, Kampong Bahru Road and Sentosa Gateway in the east; the [Keppel Harbour](/wiki/Keppel_Harbour) in the south; [West Coast Highway](/wiki/West_Coast_Highway,_Singapore) and Labrador Villa Road in the west. The area commonly known as [HarbourFront](/wiki/HarbourFront_(Singapore)) is situated at the southern portion of this subzone. [Pulau Keppel](/wiki/Keppel_Island,_Singapore) is also included as part of the territory of Maritime Square. This [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) location article is a stub.
